Performance Work Statement (PWS)
 Information Technology (IT) Support Services for the Office of Naval Research
                         Comptroller's Office (Code 08)

1.0 GENERAL

1.1 Introduction

 The Office of Naval Research (ONR) is an Echelon I headquarters organization within
 the Office of the Secretary of the Navy (SECNAV) established by Congress to command
 and manage all Science and Technology (S&T) defined as basic research (budget
 category 6.1), applied research (6.2), and advanced technology development (6.3) for the
 Department of the Navy (DON) and to foster transition from science and technology to
 higher levels of research, development, test, and evaluation.
--- Chunk #1 ---
1.2 Background

 Under the leadership of the ONR Comptroller’s Office and aligned with the DON CIO's
 data and analytics optimization strategy, the Office of Naval Research (ONR) Data and
 Analytics (D&A) Division provides oversight and coordination of financial, business,
 and technical mission support functions, including the Department of the Navy's
 Science and Technology (S&T) program, which includes basic research (6.1), applied
 research (6.2), and advanced technology development (6.3), and advises leadership on
 improving business processes, technical solutions, information management practices,
 and mission-critical data collection and reporting.
--- Chunk #2 ---
This division focuses on enhancing
 data reliability, fostering a data-proficient workforce, and accelerating cost-effective
 decision-making and analytics to maximize naval research and development
 investments, and supports the Chief of Naval Research's prioritization of data-driven
 decisions for impactful S&T portfolio and mission support outcomes by enabling
 innovative approaches to assess programmatic research, conduct program development
 reviews, implement research programs, and evaluate overall S&T portfolio
 performance.
--- Chunk #3 ---
2.0 PERFORMANCE WORK STATEMENT

 2.1 Objective

 To establish a high-value, user-centric Data and Analytics (D&A) ecosystem at the Office
 of Naval Research (ONR) that empowers strategic decision-making through: transitioning
 to a cloud-based platform; delivering impactful analytical products via the Data and
 Analytic Portal (DAP); fostering a culture of continuous improvement for D&A solutions
 and analytical tools; enabling comprehensive analysis of the S&T portfolio and mission
 support functions based on stakeholder demand signals; and driving increased adoption
 and utilization of D&A capabilities to optimize ONR's mission to foster, plan, facilitate
 and transition scientific research.
--- Chunk #4 ---
2.2 Scope

This Performance Work Statement (PWS) outlines the scope of work for Information
Technology (IT) support services required by the Office of Naval Research (ONR),
primarily for the Comptroller's Office (Code 08), the ONR Data & Analytics team
(08D), and IT efforts led by the Command Information Officer. The primary objective of
this PWS is to develop and enhance a comprehensive data and analytics environment
that delivers value-added capabilities for ONR and the Naval Research Enterprise (NRE)
mission internal stakeholders, supporting the Future Naval Power mission. This
environment must function as a trusted solution and information source.

Key Areas of Support:

 •     Data, Analytics, Visualization, Business Intelligence & Data Science:
       Provision of expertise and services to develop and enhance data-driven
       capabilities, including but not limited to:
         •  Data science methodologies and application.
         •  Business intelligence solutions.
--- Chunk #5 ---
•  Business intelligence solutions.
         •  Advanced analytics techniques.
         •  Data visualization development and implementation.

 •     IT Support: Provision of routine IT support services, including:
         •  Information Management
         •  Website and system design, development, documentation, and
            maintenance.

 •     Commercial Services: Leverage of commercial best practices and technologies to
       optimize the data and analytics environment.

Specific Tasks and Deliverables:

The Contractor shall provide the following specific support services:
 •     Data and Analytics Environment Development: Design, develop, and maintain
       a cloud-based data and analytics environment adhering to relevant policies,
       regulations, and guidance. This environment must support flexible and agile
       analytics, investigation, and informed decision-making for internal stakeholders.
--- Chunk #6 ---
This environment must support flexible and agile
       analytics, investigation, and informed decision-making for internal stakeholders.

 •     Data Integration and Management: Integrate and manage diverse data sources,
       including structured and unstructured data (Government acquisition business data,
       scientific reports and publications, and experimentation results), sourced from
       government, academic, and public sources.

 •     Application and Database Support: Design, enhance, maintain, and support
       various software and web-based (intranet/internet) applications and databases in
       support of ONR business and financial management initiatives and objectives.

 •     Portfolio Data Visualization and Tool Development: Develop multiple portfolio
       data visualizations, tools, and products to support ONR’s mission priorities.
 •     RDTE,N Budget Support: Provide programming support for all phases of the
                                                                                    Page 2
--- Chunk #7 ---
Research, Development, Test, and Evaluation, Navy (RDTE,N) budget
        formulation and execution process.

  •     Continuous Improvement and Innovation: Continuously evaluate and improve
        the data and analytics environment, deploying new and enhanced capabilities, and
        fostering innovation to reinforce the Future Naval Power mission.

  •     Website Management: Design, development, documentation, and maintenance of
        ONR websites and web-based applications.

 Expected Outcomes:

 This work will result in the following outcomes:

  •     A trusted and reliable data and analytics environment for ONR and NRE
        stakeholders.

  •     Timely and accurate data science, analytics, and visualizations to support mission-
        critical decision-making.

  •     Increased efficiency and effectiveness of ONR's business and financial
        management processes.

  •     Continuous improvement and innovation in ONR's data and analytics capabilities.

  •     Flexible and agile IT infrastructure enabling rapid response to evolving needs.
--- Chunk #8 ---
•     Increased efficiency and effectiveness of ONR's business and financial
        management processes.

  •     Continuous improvement and innovation in ONR's data and analytics capabilities.

  •     Flexible and agile IT infrastructure enabling rapid response to evolving needs.

2.3 Technical Tasks/Requirements

2.3.1 TASK 1 – PROJECT MANAGEMENT

The Contractor shall provide comprehensive project management to ensure effective
planning, execution, monitoring, and control of all work performed under this PWS. The
Contractor shall integrate cost, schedule, and technical performance across all task areas
to achieve the objectives of this requirement.

Project management activities shall include maintaining an approved Project
Management Plan (PMP), Integrated Master Schedule (IMS), and associated risk and
configuration management processes in accordance with applicable CDRLs. The
Contractor shall ensure effective coordination and communication with the ONR,
Contracting Officer’s Representative (COR), and other stakeholders to support timely
issue resolution and program transparency.
--- Chunk #9 ---
The
Contractor shall ensure effective coordination and communication with the ONR,
Contracting Officer’s Representative (COR), and other stakeholders to support timely
issue resolution and program transparency.

The Contractor shall plan and execute Transition-In and Transition-Out activities to
ensure continuity of operations and orderly handoff of responsibilities. The Contractor
shall maintain a Quality Control Plan (QCP) to ensure consistent performance and
compliance with ONR requirements.
                                                                                Page 3
--- Chunk #10 ---
All management reports, plans, meeting documentation, and related data required under
this task shall be prepared and delivered in accordance with the Contract Data
Requirements List (CDRLs). The Government will evaluate project management
performance in accordance with the Quality Assurance Surveillance Plan (QASP).

2.3.2 TASK 2 – TECHNICAL EXPERTISE

The Contractor shall provide the technical expertise, analysis, and support necessary to
develop, enhance, and sustain ONR’s Data and Analytics (D&A) environment. This
includes evaluating IT solutions, supporting data and analytics operations, developing
visualization and analytic tools, and maintaining technical documentation.

2.3.2.1. Solution Evaluation and Innovation

The Contractor shall identify, evaluate, and recommend new and emerging technologies,
tools, and methodologies to improve ONR’s D&A capabilities.
--- Chunk #11 ---
2.3.2.1. Solution Evaluation and Innovation

The Contractor shall identify, evaluate, and recommend new and emerging technologies,
tools, and methodologies to improve ONR’s D&A capabilities. This includes assessing
potential solutions for cost, performance, scalability, and compliance with Government
standards, and providing formal recommendations for consideration by ONR leadership.

2.3.2.2 Data and Analytics Operations

The Contractor shall sustain and enhance ONR’s D&A environment, providing
specialized user and help desk support, data management, and database administration.
Tasks include integrating structured and unstructured data sources, maintaining data
pipelines, and ensuring the reliability, accuracy, and timeliness of analytics products.

2.3.2.3 Analytic Tools and Visualization

The Contractor shall design, develop, and sustain authorized data visualization and
business intelligence (BI) tools to support ONR mission priorities.
--- Chunk #12 ---
2.3.2.3 Analytic Tools and Visualization

The Contractor shall design, develop, and sustain authorized data visualization and
business intelligence (BI) tools to support ONR mission priorities. Work includes
developing new dashboards, visualizations, and analytical products; maintaining legacy
BI applications; and ensuring accessibility, usability, and compliance with ONR design
standards.

2.3.2.4 Technical Documentation and Knowledge Management

The Contractor shall develop and maintain comprehensive technical, code, and process
documentation for all D&A systems and tools. This documentation shall enable
continuity of operations, knowledge transfer, and compliance with ONR and DoD
information assurance requirements. Documentation shall be reviewed and updated at
least annually or upon major system changes.
--- Chunk #13 ---
This documentation shall enable
continuity of operations, knowledge transfer, and compliance with ONR and DoD
information assurance requirements. Documentation shall be reviewed and updated at
least annually or upon major system changes.

2.3.2.5 Continuous Improvement

The Contractor shall support ONR’s culture of continuous improvement by assessing the
effectiveness of D&A tools, processes, and data pipelines; identifying efficiencies; and
recommending enhancements that align with ONR’s evolving mission and data strategy.

                                                                                   Page 4
--- Chunk #14 ---
All associated deliverables, data products, and reporting requirements are defined in the
applicable CDRLs. Performance standards and metrics for this task area are defined in
the QASP.

2.3.3 TASK 3 – TECHNICAL INFRASTRUCTURE

The Contractor shall provide comprehensive technical infrastructure support for all cloud
and web-based systems, applications, and tools supporting the Office of Naval Research
(ONR) Data and Analytics (D&A) environment. The Contractor shall ensure the
environment remains secure, scalable, reliable, and compliant with applicable DoD and
ONR cybersecurity and data protection policies.

The Contractor shall maintain and optimize cloud-hosted infrastructure environments
supporting the D&A ecosystem, including development, test, and production tiers.
Activities shall include configuration management, capacity planning, and resource
optimization to ensure effective and efficient operations within ONR-approved,
FedRAMP-authorized cloud environments (e.g., AWS GovCloud or equivalent).
--- Chunk #15 ---
Activities shall include configuration management, capacity planning, and resource
optimization to ensure effective and efficient operations within ONR-approved,
FedRAMP-authorized cloud environments (e.g., AWS GovCloud or equivalent).

The Contractor shall ensure compliance with all applicable cybersecurity, privacy, and
authorization requirements for hosting and processing sensitive information, including
Controlled Unclassified Information (CUI), Personally Identifiable Information (PII), and
mission-critical data up to Impact Level 5 (IL5). The Contractor shall support Assessment
and Authorization (A&A) activities, maintain required technical documentation and
artifacts, and coordinate with ONR’s cybersecurity personnel to ensure continuous
authorization and risk management.

The Contractor shall develop, maintain, and enhance backend services, application
programming interfaces (APIs), and integration mechanisms that enable secure and
efficient data exchange across ONR’s data and analytics platforms.
--- Chunk #16 ---
The Contractor shall develop, maintain, and enhance backend services, application
programming interfaces (APIs), and integration mechanisms that enable secure and
efficient data exchange across ONR’s data and analytics platforms. All systems shall be
documented, version controlled, and maintained in accordance with ONR configuration
management standards.

The Contractor shall ensure the ONR D&A Portal and related user-facing applications are
accessible, intuitive, and reliable. User interfaces shall comply with Section 508
accessibility requirements and provide consistent, secure access for authorized ONR
stakeholders.

If ONR transitions to new software, cloud environments, or analytic platforms during the
period of performance, the Contractor shall support the migration, integration, and
sustainment of those technologies to ensure uninterrupted service delivery and data
availability.

All associated data products, plans, and documentation requirements are defined in the
applicable Contract Data Requirements Lists (CDRLs).
