3.0 PERSONNEL REQUIREMENTS

The personnel qualifications, roles, and Full-Time Equivalent (FTE) levels described
in this section represent the Government's preliminary, notional estimate required to
successfully execute the objectives of this PWS. This information is provided as a
baseline for industry to frame responses to the Request for Information (RFI). The
Government is explicitly seeking feedback on this proposed staffing plan and
encourages respondents to propose alternative staffing models, labor categories,
and/or FTE levels that they believe would be more effective or efficient in achieving
the desired outcomes.

3.1 General Personnel Requirements and Qualifications
 The Contractor shall provide qualified personnel with the skills, experience, and
 certifications necessary to perform all tasks identified in this PWS. Personnel shall be
 capable of working independently and collaboratively in a professional environment.
--- Chunk #19 ---
Personnel shall be
 capable of working independently and collaboratively in a professional environment. The
 Contractor shall maintain adequate staffing levels to ensure continuity of operations and
 shall ensure all required certifications remain valid throughout the period of performance.
 Documentation verifying personnel qualifications, certifications, and clearance levels shall
 be maintained and provided to the Government upon request.
 All Contractor personnel must meet the following minimum qualifications:

    •  Be U.S. citizens.

    •  Possess an active Secret security clearance at the time of onboarding and have a
       minimum validity period of two years remaining.

    •  Personnel performing Information Assurance (IA) or privileged-access functions
       shall hold current certifications recognized under DoD 8570.01-M and DoD
       8140.03, appropriate to their assigned roles.

    •  Candidates must hold at least one Environment Certificate with a minimum
       validity period of one year.
--- Chunk #20 ---
•  Candidates must hold at least one Environment Certificate with a minimum
       validity period of one year.
